title: For Sale:  1958 Chevrolet Other Pickups
postcontent: Originally a Light bluish green color, you can see it behind the cab, tailgate, and under the engine compartment, this color is all over the truck, not a pieced together truck, factory Big Back Window Fleetside - Shortbox.  About 30 years ago, the truck got parked out on the ranch, and there it rested until about 2013.    A couple years ago he was saved, and built it a great little truck, the perfect patina, with the right look, people pay a lot of money these days to create this look.  This is real patina, no faux finish, this is the real deal.  No clear coat on it, this is bare beautiful surface rust.  An open canvas, drive it like it is, or take it to the next level, hopefully you leave the Patina, but if you don’t that is fine to, it is a solid little truck.   The body is in great shape, pretty obvious that it is a solid truck, very straight a few light dings and dents, the biggest in the passenger side spear, but all fixable, but it goes along with the look I think.  It does have some rust on it, besides all the surface rust.  There is some rust through in these areas.  Around the inner windshield along the gasket, the corners of the cab, the bottom  of the fenders.  Also the bottoms of the other cab, have some rust at both corners, it is dual walled and looks good from the back side.  The bed looks to be in great shape, some rust behind the back wheels under the bumper, pretty typical with the vintage Barton bumpers.  This bumper is pretty special, never saw one before, you can lay the tailgate all the way down, specially made for U.S. Forestry rigs.   The floors and inner jams all look very good no rust.  Underneath looks great, the rockers, are solid but as you can see them and dented at the bottom, but looks worse than they really are, but easy to fix, they are only single walled, and are in good shape.  There is some rust behind the passenger drivers and passenger front wheels at the bottom of the cowl, have to look up underneath the truck in fender well to see it.     The frame on the truck is in great shape, no issue, very solid no repairs.   Overall a great Rat Rod look, but on top of that, this is a very good truck, and a Rare Big Back Window Fleetside helps a lot, hard to find truck in general.  It has old plywood in the bed, with original rusty slats that have been fastened down, looks good that way I think, you could build a fancy bed if you wanted in the future.
